description:
How are we using planet Earth? From National Geographic Explorer Daniel Raven-Ellison, in 100 seconds, see our global footprint on Earth. What percent is used for agriculture? For cities? Every second represents one percent of land to understand the massive scale of the industries we rely on and just how little remains of truly wild places.
